subTitle: The host, a biologist who is an extreme angler, explores freshwater mysteries and local folklore, to debunk fascinating myths and track down harrowing tales.

title: Iberian Vipers
subTitle: The filmmaker explores the behaviour, characteristics and survival strategies of venomous vipers that inhabit the Iberian Peninsula.

title: Big Cat Tales
subTitle: Chongo is unwilling to share the buffalo with the rest of the pride while Fig continues to give lessons to the young cub.

title: China's Wild Secrets
subTitle: Spanning five of China's hidden wildlife havens, exploring some of the world's most diverse ecosystems. From lush rainforests to soaring mountains, we uncover never-before-seen animal behaviours.

title: Wild Assassins
subTitle: Wildlife experts offer detailed insights into the survival strategies employed by predators to survive the harsh climate and terrain of deserts.

title: Lion Country: Night and Day
subTitle: The narrator frets how the mothers look after their cubs and potrays a touching scene where lionesses from the same pride greet each other after a few days apart with a rough show of affection.

title: Impossible Animals
subTitle: Patrick Aryee examines the animals that live on the coast, where crashing waves to extreme tides means surviving here requires ingenuity and incredible adaptations.

title: Just Animals
subTitle: Explores the interesting facets, physical features, behaviours and habitats of a wide variety of animal species.

title: The Zoo
subTitle: Located just 10 miles from New York's Times Square, the Bronx Zoo is a recognised world leader in animal care and species conservation. It houses more than 6,000 animals and has a staff of 500-plus people dedicated to their care and well-being. Never before have camera crews been granted full access to the 265-acre campus, until production of the docuseries `The Zoo'. The results are stories focusing on dozens of animals and experiences at the facility, and its critical mission to conserve wildlife around the world. Episodes also highlight various employees and how their expertise and skills help provide top-quality care for the animals.

title: Crikey! It's the Irwins
subTitle: Carrying on late wildlife conservationist Steve Irwin's mission to bring people closer to animals is now the mission of his family. Terri, Bindi and Robert Irwin return to Animal Planet, giving viewers access to their wildlife adventures around the world and the amazing animals that continue to inspire their conservation efforts. The series features the family caring for more than 1,200 animals at the Australia Zoo; overseeing a world-class wildlife hospital, the largest of its kind in the world; and conducting high-level global expeditions.

title: Jewels of the Natural World
subTitle: Explores stunning natural landscapes and how animals act on their protective and fierce nature to survive and reproduce.

subTitle: A journey into India's wilderness highlighting some of its most iconic creatures and diverse habitats. Ranging from tundra to extreme desert, rainforest to urban jungle which provide varied ecological and geographical areas for species to survive.

subTitle: Observe the innovative teams working to preserve and protect Kenya's wildlife by deploying such tools as a radio-tracking-collar system.

title: Extreme Africa
subTitle: South Africa's Drakensberg is home to sharp climatic and ecological gradients as physical conditions change for both land-based creatures and the raptors that swirl in the skies above.

title: Extreme Africa
subTitle: Tanzania's towering northern mountains, formed by ancient volcanoes, provide diverse habitats and hold water in its great centerpiece even during the driest times.

title: Extreme Africa
subTitle: The Southern Drylands are spectacular yet treacherously arid places, harboring an array of incredibly resilient creatures.

subTitle: The guards risk their lives both to protect the tigers from the brutality of the poachers and to safeguard themselves from the attack of dangerous beasts.

subTitle: Resident veterinarians seek the assistance of domesticated elephants in order to sedate the tigers and relocate them to a secure location.
